recalls.Summary: THE BRAKE LIGHT SWITCH CAN FAIL ALLOWING THE SWITCH TO REMAIN IN THE "BRAKE LIGHTS OFF" POSITION OR IN THE "BRAKE LIGHTS ON" POSITION.
recalls.Consequence: IF THIS HAPPENS, THE BRAKE LIGHTS EITHER WILL NOT OPERATE OR WILL BE CONTINUOUSLY ON, REGARDLESS OF BRAKE PEDAL POSITION. FOLLOWING DRIVERS WOULD NOT BE ABLE TO DETERMINE WHETHER THE VEHICLE IS STOPPING, INCREASING THE POTENTIAL FOR A VEHICLE ACCIDENT.
recalls.Remedy: DEALERS WILL REPLACE THE EXISTING BRAKE LIGHT SWITCH WITH A NEWLY DESIGNED SWITCH.
recalls.Notes: SYSTEM: BRAKES; HYDRAULIC; SWITCH; BRAKE LIGHT. VEHICLE DESCRIPTION: PASSENGER VEHICLES. OWNER NOTIFICATION: OWNER NOTIFICATION IS EXPECTED TO BEGIN AUGUST 5, 1996. NOTE: OWNERS WHO TAKE THEIR VEHICLES TO AN AUTHORIZED DEALER ON AN AGREED UPON SERVICE DATE AND DO NOT RECEIVE THE FREE REMEDY WITHIN A REASONABLE TIME SHOULD CONTACT BMW AT 1-800-831-1117. ALSO CONTACT THE NATIONAL HIGHWAY TRAFFIC SAFETY ADMINISTRATION'S AUTO SAFETY HOTLINE AT 1-800-424-9393.

recalls.Summary: IN A FMVSS NO. 208 30 MILES-PER-HOUR COMPLIANCE TEST, AN UNBELTED TEST DRIVER DUMMY'S CHEST MAXIMUM RESULTANT ACCELERATION WAS 70.8 G'S, WHICH EXCEEDS THE MAXIMUM ALLOWABLE VALUE OF 60 G'S. ALSO, THE UNBELTED PASSENGER DUMMY'S LEFT FEMUR MAXIMUM LOAD WAS 2361 LBS, WHICH EXCEEDS MAXIMUM ALLOWABLE VALUE OF 2250 LBS. THE VEHICLES DO NOT COMPLY WITH FMVSS NO. 208, "OCCUPANT CRASH PROTECTION."
recalls.Consequence: CONSEQUENCE OF NON-COMPLIANCE:  IN THE EVENT OF AN ACCIDENT, THE OCCUPANT WILL BE SUBJECTED TO AN INCREASED RISK OF INJURY.
recalls.Remedy: ON AUTOMATIC TRANSMISSION MODELS ONLY, THE DEALER WILL REPLACE THE TRANSMISSION SUPPORT CROSSMEMBER WITH A CROSSMEMBER USED ON THE MANUAL TRANSMISSION MODEL. ALSO, THE TRANSMISSION REAR BUSHING SUPPORTS WILL BE REPLACED WITH BUSHING HAVING DIFFERENT PERFORMANCE CHARACTERISTICS. THE STEERING COLUMN FRONT SUPPORT BEARING AT THE FIREWALL WILL BE REPLACED WITH A MODIFIED PART USING A TEFLON INNER SURFACE AND TEFLON SPRAY WILL BE APPLIED TO THE COLUMN HOUSING IN THE AREA OF THE BEARING. A BRACE WILL BE ADDED BETWEEN THE KNEE BOLSTER SUPPORT AND THE STEERING COLUMN.
recalls.Notes: SYSTEM: INTERIOR SYSTEMS; PASSIVE RESTRAINTS; AIR BAG; DRIVER; FMVSS N0. 208.  VEHICLE DESCRIPTION: PASSENGER CARS, MODELS 325I, 325IA, 325IS, 325SA, AND M3.  NOTE: IF YOUR VEHICLE IS PRESENTED TO AN AUTHORIZED DEALER ON AN AGREED UPON SERVICE DATE AND THE REMEDY IS NOT PROVIDED FREE OF CHARGE WITHIN A REASONABLE TIME OR THE REMEDY DOES NOT CORRECT THE NONCOMPLIANCE, PLEASE CONTACT BMW SERVICE CENTER AT 1-800-831-1117. ALSO, CONTACT THE NATIONAL HIGHWAY TRAFFIC SAFETY ADMINISTRATION'S AUTO SAFETY HOTLINE AT 1-800-424-9393.

recalls.Summary: THE CRUISE CONTROL AND THROTTLE CABLES ARE ATTACHED TO THE SAME THROTTLE VALVE ACTUATING LEVER AT THE THROTTLE HOUSING.  IT IS POSSIBLE THAT THE PLASTIC BUSHING ON EITHER CABLE COULD BREAK DUE TO ENVIRONMENTAL INFLUENCES COUPLED WITH VIBRATION.  IF THE BUSHING BREAKS, THE OUTER CABLE HOUSING CAN SEPARATE FROM THE BUSHING.   IN THIS CASE, DURING APPLICATION OF THE THROTTLE PEDAL WITHOUT CRUISE CONTROL BEING ENGAGED, THE OUTER TUBE COULD CATCH ON THE EDGE OF THE BROKEN BUSHING.
recalls.Consequence: THIS COULD CAUSE THE THROTTLE VALVE TO REMAIN PARTIALLY OPEN.  IT HIS WERE TO OCCUR, THE CAR MIGHT NOT DECELERATE AS EXPECTED INCREASING THE RISK OF A VEHICLE CRASH.
recalls.Remedy: DEALERS WILL INSTALL A SPRING STEEL CLIP ON THE OUTER TUBE OF EACH CABLE IN THE AREA OF THE ADJUSTING SCREW AND PLASTIC BUSHING.  THE CLIP IS DESIGNED TO PREVENT THE OUTER TUBE FROM DISLODGING FROM THE BUSHING.
recalls.Notes: OWNER NOTIFICATION IS EXPECTED TO BEGIN BY THE END OF OCTOBER 1997.   OWNERS WHO TAKE THEIR VEHICLES TO AN AUTHORIZED DEALER ON AN AGREED UPON SERVICE DATE AND DO NOT RECEIVE THE FREE REMEDY WITHIN A REASONABLE TIME SHOULD CONTACT BMW AT 1-800-831-1117.  ALSO CONTACT THE NATIONAL HIGHWAY TRAFFIC SAFETY ADMINISTRATION'S AUTO SAFETY HOTLINE AT 1-800-424-9393.

recalls.Summary: VEHICLE DESCRIPTION:  PASSENGER VEHICLES.  A MALFUNCTION OR FAILURE OF A COOLANT SYSTEM COMPONENT, SUCH AS A THERMOSTAT, WATER PUMP, OR FAN BELT, CAN RESULT IN SIGNIFICANTLY INCREASED COOLANT TEMPERATURE AND SYSTEM PRESSURE.  IF THE INDICATIONS OF A CRITICAL OVERHEATING CONDITION IS NOT NOTICED BY THE DRIVER, IT IS POSSIBLE THAT DAMAGE TO, OR FAILURE OF, A COOLANT SYSTEM COMPONENT COULD OCCUR.
recalls.Consequence: IF A CRACK WERE TO FORM OR A SEAM WERE TO SEPARATE IN THE HEATER CORE END PIECE, HOT COOLANT COULD SUDDENLY BE EXPELLED, INCREASING THE RISK OF PERSONAL INJURY TO A VEHICLE OCCUPANT.
recalls.Remedy: DEALERS WILL INSTALL A NEW DESIGN RADIATOR CAP TO CONTROL PRESSURE AND PROVIDE GREATER COOLANT OVERFLOW IN THE EVENT OF OVERHEATING.
recalls.Notes: OWNER NOTIFICATION BEGAN MARCH 31, 1999.   OWNERS WHO TAKE THEIR VEHICLES TO AN AUTHORIZED DEALER ON AN AGREED UPON SERVICE DATE AND DO NOT RECEIVE THE FREE REMEDY WITHIN A REASONABLE TIME SHOULD CONTACT BMW AT 1-800-831-1117.  ALSO CONTACT THE NATIONAL HIGHWAY TRAFFIC SAFETY ADMINISTRATION'S AUTO SAFETY HOTLINE AT 1-888-DASH-2-DOT (1-888-327-4236).

issues.title: Cooling System Failure
issues.description: The cooling system components including radiator, water pump, thermostat, and expansion tank are prone to failure, leading to overheating issues that can cause severe engine damage
issues.fix_description: Replace faulty cooling system components including radiator, water pump, thermostat, expansion tank, and hoses
issues.prevention: Regular coolant flushes, inspect cooling system components regularly, replace aging plastic components proactively

issues.title: VANOS System Failure
issues.description: The variable valve timing system (VANOS) seals deteriorate over time, causing rattling noises, poor idle, and reduced engine performance
issues.fix_description: Replace VANOS seals, solenoids, and perform timing chain inspection
issues.prevention: Use high quality oil, change oil frequently (every 5000 miles), avoid extended idle periods

issues.title: Rear Subframe Cracking
issues.description: The rear subframe mounting points are prone to cracking due to stress from the powerful engine and aggressive driving, potentially causing catastrophic handling issues
issues.fix_description: Weld reinforcement plates or replace entire rear subframe assembly
issues.prevention: Avoid hard launches, regular inspection of subframe, install reinforcement plates preventatively

issues.title: Rod Bearing Failure
issues.description: The connecting rod bearings can fail prematurely, especially in high-mileage vehicles or those subjected to aggressive driving, resulting in catastrophic engine damage
issues.fix_description: Complete engine rebuild or replacement, replace all rod bearings and related components
issues.prevention: Frequent oil changes with high-quality oil, avoid over-revving, monitor oil pressure regularly

issues.title: Window Regulator Failure
issues.description: Power window regulators commonly fail, causing windows to fall into the door or become inoperable
issues.fix_description: Replace window regulator mechanism and motor if necessary
issues.prevention: Avoid forcing stuck windows, lubricate window tracks regularly

issues.title: Oil Pump Nut Backing Off
issues.description: The oil pump retention nut can back off, causing complete loss of oil pressure and immediate engine failure
issues.fix_description: Remove oil pan, re-torque or replace oil pump nut with thread locker, inspect for damage
issues.prevention: Inspect oil pump nut during oil changes, apply proper thread locker during assembly

issues.title: Fuel Tank Evaporative System Issues
issues.description: The fuel tank ventilation system and carbon canister can fail, causing fuel vapor issues and check engine lights
issues.fix_description: Replace carbon canister, purge valve, and associated vacuum lines
issues.prevention: Don't top off fuel tank, replace fuel cap if damaged, regular emissions system inspection

issues.title: Differential Mount Failure
issues.description: The rear differential mount deteriorates, causing excessive drivetrain movement and vibration under acceleration
issues.fix_description: Replace rear differential mount with reinforced aftermarket unit
issues.prevention: Avoid hard launches, inspect mounts during regular service

issues.title: Instrument Cluster Pixel Failure
issues.description: LCD pixels in the instrument cluster fail over time, making it difficult to read certain information
issues.fix_description: Replace instrument cluster or repair LCD display professionally
issues.prevention: Avoid extreme temperatures, protect dashboard from direct sunlight

issues.title: Intake Manifold Vacuum Leaks
issues.description: Rubber intake boot and vacuum hoses deteriorate over time, causing vacuum leaks that affect engine performance
issues.fix_description: Replace intake boot, vacuum hoses, and clean throttle body
issues.prevention: Regular inspection of rubber components, replace aging vacuum lines proactively

issues.title: Clutch Disc and Flywheel Wear
issues.description: The clutch system experiences accelerated wear due to the high torque output, requiring frequent replacement
issues.fix_description: Replace clutch disc, pressure plate, release bearing, and resurface or replace flywheel
issues.prevention: Proper clutch technique, avoid riding the clutch, don't launch hard repeatedly

issues.title: Shock Tower Mushrooming
issues.description: The front shock towers can develop stress cracks and mushrooming due to the stiff suspension setup
issues.fix_description: Reinforce shock towers with plates or replace tower assembly
issues.prevention: Install shock tower reinforcement plates, avoid aggressive driving over poor road surfaces

editorial.tagline: The last pure, naturally-aspirated M3 masterpiece
editorial.hero_blurb: The E36 M3 represents BMW's final commitment to naturally-aspirated perfection before the turbo era. This is the M3 that carved canyons and conquered hearts with surgical precision and an intoxicating straight-six symphony.
editorial.essence: The E36 M3 embodies the sweet spot of M Division's evolution - sophisticated enough to be civilized daily, yet raw enough to deliver pure driving euphoria. It's the last M3 that prioritized feel over figures, creating an emotional connection that modern cars struggle to match.
editorial.heritage: Born from the E30's racing success, the E36 M3 evolved the formula with more power, better aerodynamics, and refined chassis dynamics. It carried forward M Division's motorsport DNA while establishing the template for modern performance sedans.
editorial.design_philosophy: BMW's engineers sought to create the ultimate balance between everyday usability and track-ready performance. Every component was tuned for driver engagement, from the progressive suspension to the perfectly weighted controls.
editorial.motorsport_history: Dominated touring car championships worldwide, including BTCC, WTCC, and American club racing. Its success on track directly translated to the road car's legendary reputation for being a born racer.
editorial.engine_character: The S50/S52 delivers power with silky smoothness that builds to a crescendo at 7,000 RPM. It's an engine that rewards commitment, producing its best when worked hard, with linear power delivery that makes every gear change addictive.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 5-speed manual offers mechanical precision with satisfying weight and defined gates. Each shift feels purposeful, with short throws that encourage quick, confident gear changes during spirited driving.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Perfectly balanced with neutral handling that can rotate on throttle lift or settle into composed understeer depending on driver input. The chassis communicates every nuance of the road surface while maintaining remarkable composure.
editorial.steering_feel: Hydraulic steering provides genuine feedback with appropriate weight that builds naturally with speed. The connection between hands and front wheels is direct and informative, making precise placement effortless.
editorial.brake_confidence: Strong, progressive brakes with excellent pedal feel that inspire confidence during aggressive driving. They provide consistent performance with good heat resistance for extended track sessions or mountain runs.
editorial.sound_signature: A sophisticated straight-six note that ranges from refined purr at idle to an aggressive, metallic wail at redline. The exhaust note is distinctly BMW - purposeful without being crude, musical without being artificial.
editorial.ideal_owner: Driving purists who value mechanical connection over outright speed, collectors seeking the last analog M3, or weekend warriors who want a car that excels on both street and track.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Those seeking modern convenience features, buyers wanting maximum straight-line performance, or anyone not prepared for higher maintenance costs and potential reliability issues with aging performance components.
editorial.buyers_summary: Look for well-maintained examples with service records, as these cars require proper care to remain at their best. Prices are climbing steadily as enthusiasts recognize the E36 M3's significance as the end of an era.

expertReviews.title: 250000 mile 1998 BMW M3 - E36 Ownership Review
pros: Excellent handling and balance with OEM+ modifications
Reliable S52 inline-6 engine even at high mileage
Great shifting feel with short shifter and clutch upgrade
Good fuel economy (32 mpg highway when driven efficiently)
cons: Check engine light with Vanos code causing occasional hesitation
Sunroof vibration at higher speeds
Some NVH from solid differential bushings
Previous head gasket failure at high mileage
Minor clutch smell during spirited driving
AC robs noticeable power when engaged
Requires track-specific upgrades for reliability
expertReviews.verdict: This high-mileage E36 M3 demonstrates the platform's potential when properly maintained and modified. With 250,000+ miles, the car still delivers excellent performance thanks to thoughtful OEM+ modifications including suspension, differential bushings, cooling upgrades, and drivetrain improvements. Despite minor issues like the Vanos code and some NVH from solid bushings, the reviewer considers this the best E36 they've driven, praising its balance, handling, and character. The car proves that with proper care and upgrades, these BMWs can remain engaging and reliable track weapons well into high mileage.

expertReviews.title: 1999 BMW M3 (E36) | The Reason I Fell In Love With BMW
pros: Well-balanced chassis that communicates road feel without being harsh
Classic BMW interior design and ergonomics
Excellent styling that was 'nailed' according to reviewer
Lighter weight compared to newer generations allows for good compliance
Instills confidence at speed while remaining communicative
cons: Steering feels light with deadness around center
Long clutch and gear shift throws
Seating position requires sitting close to wheel, especially for taller drivers
Brakes are gradual and non-linear in initial travel
Less sharp and immediate than E46 generation
240hp feels underpowered compared to 316hp European version
expertReviews.verdict: The E36 M3 offers a unique 'ease' character that sits perfectly between the raw E30 and sharp E46 generations. While not as immediate or sharp as newer BMWs, it provides excellent communication and balance. The S52 engine is smooth and responsive, the chassis communicates beautifully without being harsh, and the overall experience is one of confident, comfortable performance. A compelling middle ground that showcases classic BMW virtues.

expertReviews.title: 1997 BMW E36 M3 Review - Manual Swapped $10K Bargain?
pros: Linear smooth inline-6 engine with good torque
cons: Heavy and grabby Stage 2 clutch not ideal for daily driving
Interior doesn't age well
Rubber shifter feel despite short shifter
Low grip ceiling with cheap tires
ABS and traction control not working
Loose shift knob
expertReviews.verdict: For under $10,000, this manual-swapped E36 M3 offers exceptional driving dynamics and value. The natural balance, communicative steering, and smooth S52 engine make it an excellent budget sports sedan choice. While it has some budget build compromises like the grabby clutch and cheap suspension, the core driving experience remains outstanding.

expertReviews.title: Here's What Its Like Driving A 27 Year Old E36 M3 With 82720 ...
pros: Light weight and tossable at 3200 lbs
Easy to use clutch and shifter
Accessible speed for street and canyon driving
cons: Cheap plastic interior materials from 90s era
Fixed seat bolsters lack adjustability and support
Lower power output compared to Euro spec
Some vagueness in shifter feel
Small cabin size compared to modern cars
expertReviews.verdict: The E36 M3 is a fantastic driver's car that excels in feel and handling over raw power. Despite being US-spec with 240hp, it's plenty quick and more than makes up for lower power with excellent driving dynamics, lightweight chassis, and old-school M formula. Highly recommended for those seeking a pure driving experience.

expertReviews.title: 1999 E36 BMW M3 - POV Driving Impressions
pros: Good turning radius and steering feel
cons: Long clutch throw
Body roll and handling sloppy by modern standards
Maintenance hungry ownership
Creaky seats
Little bit off-center driving position
Traction control intervention
Requires deliberate inputs
Fast rev drop requires quick shifts
expertReviews.verdict: The E36 M3 represents an engaging and refreshing driving experience that serves as a reset from modern cars. With its characterful S52 inline-6, classic BMW shifter, and involving ownership experience, it offers great practicality and driving fun. This particular example is a rare survivor in excellent condition with desirable options. Values have climbed to low-mid $20s for nice examples, making it an icon from BMW's great era that's increasingly hard to find in pristine condition.

expertReviews.title: The Cheaper E36 M3 Alternative? | BMW 328i E36 Review | Driven+
pros: Beautiful Lila metallic paint - one of only 24 worldwide
Classic BMW straight-six engine sound and feel
Affordable at around 4,000 compared to M3
Great project car potential with modification possibilities
Timeless E36 design with proper-sized kidney grilles
Pure driving experience - RWD, manual, naturally aspirated
Well-equipped interior with heated seats and trip computer
cons: Prone to rust issues due to age
Heavy at 1,400kg for its size
Not particularly fast by modern standards
Most examples found are automatic rather than manual
Interior prone to sagging headliner
No cup holders as standard
expertReviews.verdict: The 328i makes an excellent alternative to the expensive E36 M3, offering the classic BMW straight-six experience at a fraction of the cost. While not as fast as modern cars, it provides pure driving enjoyment through its rear-wheel drive, manual transmission setup. Perfect as a project car for modifications or track use, though buyers should be aware of rust issues typical of older BMWs.
